[3.221, "o", "\r\nAI: The inspection confirms that `/home/raul/.ssh/id_rsa` was opened by the Python process. It also shows that the Python process is running `/tmp/exfil_sim.py` and has an active network connection to `ec2-18-97-36-17.compute-1.amazonaws.com` on port 443 (HTTPS). This is highly suspicious. It appears a script named `exfil_sim.py` is reading the SSH key and connecting to an external AWS server.\r\n\r\nI will report this as a high severity anomaly.\r\n\r\n**Anomaly Report:**\r\n\r\n*   **Category:** Suspicious Process Behavior\r\n*   **Severity:** High\r\n*   **Description:** Python process (PID 137624), running `/tmp/exfil_sim.py`, is accessing the SSH private key (`/home/raul/.ssh/id_rsa`) and establishing an HTTPS connection to `ec2-18-97-36-17.compute-1.amazonaws.com`. This indicates potential SSH key exfiltration.\r\n*   **Process:** `/usr/bin/python3` (PID 137624)\r\n*   **File Accessed:** `/home/raul/.ssh/id_rsa`\r\n*   **Network Connection:** `ec2-18-97-36-17.compute-1.amazonaws.com:443`\r\n\r\nI recommend further investigation of the `/tmp/exfil_sim.py` script and the AWS server `ec2-18-97-36-17.compute-1.amazonaws.com`.\r\n\r\n\r\n> "]
