[5.942, "o", "\r\nAI: Okay, here's a summary of the system as of the latest snapshot (2026-03-09T17:17:04-06:00):\r\n\r\n**Major Active Process Groups:**\r\n\r\n*   **/system/bin/app\\_process64:** This is a core Android process, running multiple instances, likely hosting various Android apps and services. Some instances are showing relatively high CPU usage.\r\n*   **/usr/lib/electron39/electron:** This indicates the presence of Electron-based applications. `gopls` (Go language server) and `/usr/lib/antigravity/extensions/antigravity/bin/language_server_linux_x64` appear to be running under Electron.\r\n*   **/usr/bin/pipewire:** PipeWire is a multimedia framework for handling audio and video.\r\n*   **/opt/google/chrome/chrome:** Google Chrome browser is running.\r\n*   **/vendor/bin/hw/android.hardware.graphics.composer@2.1-service:** Android graphics service.\r\n*   **/usr/bin/python3:** A Python 3 interpreter is running. Notably, it was flagged as part of a high-severity anomaly due to its access to the SSH private key and connection to a suspicious AWS server.\r\n*   **/usr/bin/wireplumber:** WirePlumber is a session/policy manager for PipeWire.\r\n*   **/usr/bin/btop:** A system monitoring tool.\r\n*   **/usr/bin/zsh:** The Z shell is running.\r\n*   **/system/bin/lmkd:** Low Memory Killer Daemon (Android).\r\n*   **/usr/bin/waybar:** A highly configurable Wayland bar.\r\n*   **/usr/bin/yazi:** A terminal file manager.\r\n*   **/system/bin/audioserver:** Android audio server.\r\n*   **/system/bin/logd:** Android logging daemon.\r\n\r\n**Recently Exited Processes:**\r\n\r\nA large number of `hyprctl`, `git`, `cliphist`, `starship`, `cat`, and `zsh` processes have recently exited. The frequent execution of `hyprctl` warrants a check.\r\n\r\n**Key Observations and Potential Issues:**\r\n\r\n*   **SSH Key Exfiltration:** The Python process (/usr/bin/python3, PID 137624) running `/tmp/exfil_sim.py` is a major security concern. It's actively reading the SSH private key and connecting to a suspicious external server.\r\n*   **Android Processes:** High CPU usage in some Android processes may indicate performance issues or resource contention.\r\n*   **Electron Apps:** The presence of Electron apps is normal, but their resource usage should be monitored.\r\n\r\nIn summary, the system appears to be functioning, but the SSH key exfiltration incident requires immediate attention. The other processes seem normal for a development environment, but resource usage should be monitored.\r\n\r\n\r\n> "]
