[2.817, "o", "\r\nAI: The search results confirm that the recently exited `git` processes (140061, 140062, 140063, 140064) were spawned by the electron app. Moreover, the electron app and its libuv-worker child are accessing git related files in `/home/raul/Desktop/projects/godshell/.git/`. This further supports the theory that the electron app is related to the `godshell` project.\r\n\r\nBased on my analysis of the summary and related processes, the activity appears to be related to a development environment for the `godshell` project. The electron app is likely an IDE or related tool, and the git processes are probably being used for version control. While the electron app could potentially be malicious, in this context, it seems more likely to be part of the development workflow.\r\n\r\nTherefore, I don't see anything particularly weird happening in the system that isn't explained by the presence of a development environment.\r\n\r\n\r\n> "]
