[2.076, "o", "\r\nAI: Process 110041 is a `zsh` shell, and its parent is process 110031. It spawned python. It is also spawning children that are quickly exiting. This reinforces that it may be a malicious process. It is very likely that this process is running the exfiltration simulation script.\r\n\r\nI conclude that there is indeed something weird happening. A python script `/tmp/exfil_sim.py` is being executed from a zsh shell (PID 110041), and it's connecting to an AWS server. This is highly suspicious and warrants further investigation.\r\n\r\n\r\n> "]
