[3.505, "o", "\r\nAI: You're asking whether I can perform runtime analysis of the `com.miruta.mty` application's binaries within the Waydroid environment. While I can access process metadata (memory maps, file handles, etc.), I cannot perform more advanced runtime analysis techniques such as:\r\n\r\n*   **Code disassembly/decompilation:** I can't directly disassemble the in-memory code of the Urbani app or decompile it into a higher-level language.\r\n*   **Dynamic instrumentation:** I can't inject code or hooks into the Urbani process to trace its execution, monitor API calls, or modify its behavior.\r\n*   **Memory dumping:** I can't dump the entire memory space of the Urbani process to analyze its contents offline.\r\n\r\nThese limitations are in place because it's not possible with the current tools.\r\n\r\n\r\n> "]
