[1.844, "o", "\r\nAI: I've reviewed the memory maps for both PID 99719 and PID 141542, which are \"tokio-runtime-w\" processes associated with \"/usr/bin/yazi\". Neither process has any memory regions with rwx (read, write, execute) permissions. The permissions observed are combinations of read, write, execute, and private/shared flags (r, w, x, p, s). There are 'rw-p' regions, but no 'rwx' regions, and there are 'r-xp' regions, but these are read-execute only. Therefore, yazi does not have rwx memory.\r\n\r\n\r\n> "]
