[1.894, "o", "\r\nAI: The linked libraries for the language server don't immediately show anything out of the ordinary.\r\n\r\nGiven that both the language server and its parent Electron process are connecting to a WhatsApp CDN, I suspect a potential compromise or misconfiguration of the Antigravity IDE. It is possible that an extension or component within the IDE is the source of the connections. It's also possible that this is benign traffic due to a poorly configured extension, but given that it's a CDN for WhatsApp, it seems more likely to be malicious. Further investigation is warranted.\r\n\r\n> "]
